</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id7a87b881-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s8519/a/1/C"><num value="C">(C)</num><content> $20,000,000 is authorized for the joint technology transfer initiative described in <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s8512/b/4">section 8512(b)(4) of this title</ref>;</content>
</subparagraph>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a87b882-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s8519/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><chapeau> $148,154,000 for fiscal year 2020, of which—</chapeau><subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id7a87b883-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s8519/a/2/A"><num value="A">(A)</num><content> $87,258,000 is authorized for weather laboratories and cooperative institutes;</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id7a87b884-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s8519/a/2/B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content> $40,896,000 is authorized for weather and air chemistry research programs; and</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id7a87b885-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s8519/a/2/C"><num value="C">(C)</num><content> $20,000,000 is authorized for the joint technology transfer initiative described in <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s8512/b/4">section 8512(b)(4) of this title</ref>;</content>
</subparagraph>
