<notes type="uscNote" id="id7a87b894-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7a87b895-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="id7a87b896-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">This subchapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this title”, meaning title I of <ref href="/us/pl/115/25">Pub. L. 115–25</ref>, which enacted this subchapter and amended provisions formerly set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s313">section 313 of this title</ref>, which is now classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s8520">section 8520 of this title</ref>. For complete classification of title I to the Code, see Tables.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The amendments made by this title, referred to in subsec. (b), mean the amendments made by title I of <ref href="/us/pl/115/25">Pub. L. 115–25</ref>, which amended provisions formerly set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s313">section 313 of this title</ref> and which is now classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s8520">section 8520 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id7a87b897-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2019—<ref href="/us/pl/115/423">Pub. L. 115–423</ref> amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section related to authorization of appropriations for fiscal years 2017 and 2018.</p>
</note>
</notes>
